<topic class="Popup" template="Default" status="Under Construction" modified="2024-02-05T19:08:31.583Z" lasteditedby="44785" version="2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title>Dimension Measurement</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Definition<keyword>Dimension: Measurement</keyword></keyword>
    <keyword>Driven Dimension</keyword>
    <keyword>Late Gearing</keyword>
    <keyword>Measurement</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Measurement FB</text>, (see <text styleclass="T_Menusmall">Kinematic FB toolbar &gt;</text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-AddFBMeasurement" styleclass="T_Menusmall">Add Measurement FB</link>, displays the distance or angle between two(2) <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Lines</text> or the angle between three(3) <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Points</text> (In the special case where the selected sketch-elements are in different <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Mechanism-Editors</text>, it is called a Reference Dimension). The <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Measurement FB</text> gives the dimension and the first and second motion-derivatives (rate-of-change of the dimension) at its output-connector.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The dimension in the graphics-area next to the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Measurement FB </text>is equivalent to a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">driven-dimension</text>. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">You can use use the motion-values at the output-connector from a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Measurement FB</text> as the motion-values for a different <text styleclass="VariableName-small">kinematic-chain</text>. We use the term <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Late-Gearing</text> to identify those <text styleclass="VariableName-small">kinematic-chains</text> driven by the motion-values from a different <text styleclass="VariableName-small">kinematic-chain</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="SeeAlso-small">See also: </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Dimension-Reference-Measurement" styleclass="SeeAlso-small">Reference Dimension</link><text styleclass="SeeAlso-small">, &apos;</text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Dimension-Static" styleclass="SeeAlso-small">Static&apos; Dimension</link><text styleclass="SeeAlso-small">, </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-AddFBMeasurement" styleclass="SeeAlso-small">Add Measurement FB</link><text styleclass="SeeAlso-small">.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
